t=|first=|url=https://www.philenews.com/koinonia/eidiseis/article/895538/koronoios-nea-kroysmata-kai-nea-metra|title=Coronavirus: New outbreaks and new measures|date=|work=PhileNews|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> [[President of Cyprus|President]] [[Nicos Anastasiades]], in a special appearance, announced the closing of all borders except for nationals for 15 days from 15 March.<ref>{{cite web | title=UPDATE 1-Cyprus shuts its borders for 15 days to fight coronavirus| website=[[Reuters]]| date=2020-03-13 | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-cyprus-borders/update-1-cyprus-shuts-its-borders-for-15-days-to-fight-coronavirus-idUSL8N2B67EA| access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref>\n* On 21 March, the first death was confirmed.<ref>{{cite web | title=Cyprus reports its first coronavirus death - health ministry| website=[[Reuters]]| date=2020-03-21 | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-cyprus-death/cyprus-reports-its-first-coronavirus-death-health-ministry-idUSA8N29K01J| access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Michael |first1=Peter |title=Nine new confirmed cases, one a nurse from Paphos hospital |url=https://cyprus-mail.com/2020/03/21/coronavirus-nine-new-confirmed-cases-one-a-nurse-from-paphos-hospital/ |work=Cyprus Mail |date=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n* on 25 March Eight New Cases were confirmed.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Malik |first1=Nomi |title=Eight new Cases of Coronavirus and two more dead and a total of 124 Cases |url=https://daily-cyprus.com/2020/03/24/eight-new-cases-of-coronavirus-and-two-more-dead-and-a-total-of-124-cases/ |work=Daily Cyprus News |publisher=Daily Cyprus News |date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n* on 26 March 14 New Cases were confirmed.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ministry of Health Confirmed 14 new cases of Coronavirus |url=https://daily-cyprus.com/2020/03/26/ministry-of-health-confirmed-14-new-cases-of-coronavirus/ |work=Daily Cyprus News |date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n* on 27 March 16 New Cases were confirmed and 2 deaths.<ref>{{cite news |title=16 new cases of Coronavirus and two died from Covid-19 |url=https://daily-cyprus.com/2020/03/27/16-new-cases-of-coronavirus-and-two-died-from-covid-19/ |work=Daily Cyprus News |date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n* on 3 April 40 New Cases were confirmed and 1 death.<ref>{{cite news |title=40 new cases of Coronavirus, One Death and total reached to 396 |url=https://daily-cyprus.com/2020/04/03/40-new-cases-of-coronavirus-and-total-reached-to-396/ |work=Daily Cyprus News |date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n* on 4 April 30 New Cases were Confirmed.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://daily-cyprus.com/2020/04/04/30-new-cases-of-coronavirus-and-total-426/|title=30 new cases of Coronavirus and total 426|date=|work=Daily Cyprus News|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* on 5 April 20 New Cases were Confirmed.<ref>{{cite news|last=|first=|url=https://daily-cyprus.com/2020/04/05/20-new-cases-and-one-death/|title=20 new cases of Coronavirus|date=5 April 2020|work=Daily Cyprus News|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Cyprus medical cases chart}}\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|width=800\n|colors=#F46D43\n|showValues=\n|showSymbols=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|yAxisTitle=Total confirmed cases\n|type=line\n|x=8 Mar, 9 Mar, 10 Mar, 11 Mar, 12 Mar, 13 Mar, 14 Mar, 15 Mar, 16 Mar, 17 Mar, 18 Mar, 19 Mar, 20 Mar, 21 Mar, 22 Mar, 23 Mar, 24 Mar, 25 Mar, 26 Mar, 27 Mar, 28 Mar, 29 Mar, 30 Mar, 31 Mar, 1 Apr, 2 Apr, 3 Apr, 4 Apr, 5 Apr\n|y1=0, 2, 2, 6, 10, 21, 26, 33, 46, 49, 58, 67, 75, 84, 95, 116, 124, 132, 146, 162, 179, 214, 230, 262, 320, 356, 396, 426, 446\n|yGrid= |xGrid=\n}}\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|width=800\n|colors=#F46D43\n|showValues=offset:2\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|yAxisTitle=No. of new cases\n|type=rect\n|x=8 Mar, 9 Mar, 10 Mar, 11 Mar, 12 Mar, 13 Mar, 14 Mar, 15 Mar, 16 Mar, 17 Mar, 18 Mar, 19 Mar, 20 Mar, 21 Mar, 22 Mar, 23 Mar, 24 Mar, 25 Mar, 26 Mar, 27 Mar, 28 Mar, 29 Mar, 30