es: Approaches, Evidence and Ways Forward. The Open University Working Paper No 41.\n*{{cite journal | last1 = Rahman | first1 = A | year = 1999 | title = Micro-credit Initiatives for Equitable and Sustainable Development: Who Pays? | url = | journal = World Development | volume = 27 | issue = 1| pages = 67\u201382 | doi=10.1016/s0305-750x(98)00105-3}}\n*CHESTON, S. and KUHN, L. (2002). Empowering Women through Microfinance. Pathways Out of Poverty: Innovations in Microfinance for the Poorest Families.\n*Harper, A. ( 1995). Providing women in Baltistan with access to loans \u2013 potential and problems. Lahore, AKRSP Pakistan.\n*Mutalima, I. K., 2006, [http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20100114105356/http%3A//www.microcreditsummit.org/papers/Workshops/28_Mutalima.pdf Microfinance and Gender Equality: Are We Getting There?]: Micro Credit Summit, Halifa, Royal Tropical Institute and Oxfam Novib.\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.grameen-info.org/what-is-microcredit/ What is Microcredit]\n* [http://www.povertyactionlab.org/publication/latest-findings-randomized-evaluations-microfinance Latest Findings from Randomized Evaluations of Microfinance] Access to Finance Forum by CGAP and Its Partners No. 2, December 2011\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070716100213/http://www.usaid.gov/locations/sub-saharan_africa/sudan/ss_microfinance.html Building a Microfinance Institution from Scratch] Institution's objective is to offer financial services on a self-sustaining yet efficient basis to microentrepreneurs.\n* [http://www.lib.byu.edu/spc/microfinance/ Journal of Microfinance], a forum for practitioners in microfinance and microenterprise development to exchange information and ideas\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060430010701/http://www.tufts.edu/microfinancefund/ Omidyar-Tufts Microfinance Fund], a partnership between [[Pierre Omidyar]] and [[Tufts University]].\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070815104804/http://thehague.usembassy.gov/mrs._arnall_microfinance \"Microfinance in the U.S.\"] Helping ensure egalitarian access to needed financial services.\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070812061759/http://www.csa.com/discoveryguides/microfinance/review.php The Promise of Microfinance for Poverty Relief in the Developing World]\n*[http://www.mra.gov.bd/ Microcredit Regulatory Authority, MRA] The central body to monitor and supervise microfinance operation of NGOs of Bangladesh\n*[http://www.brac.net/ Alleviation and poverty and empowerment of the poor, BRAC] [[Bangladesh]]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20091231170553/http://www.credit-coops.ru/ The European Union Project \"Credit Cooperatives \u2013 Russian Federation\"] official web site\n*[http://www.kbyutv.org/smallfortunes/ Small Fortunes: Microcredit and the Future of Poverty] web site for a [[PBS]] documentary\n\n{{Consumer debt}}\n\n[[Category:Microfinance]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi inventions]]\n[[Category:Irish inventions]]\n[[Category:Pakistani inventions]]\n", "name_user": "Itstyagi", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microcredit"}
